The paper discusses the evolution of programmable networking and automation of optical networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the role of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in smart optical networks, which falls under the category of AI (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE) in smart optical networks.
